We want to find the sum of an arithmetic sequence, where the first term is 28, the last term is 1, and the common difference is $25 - 28 = -3.$  The number of terms in this sequence is $\frac{28 - 1}{-3} + 1 = 10,$ so
\begin{align*}
\frac{28 + 1}{2} \cdot 10 &= \boxed{145}.
\end{align*}
